Note = {International Conference on Automation, Quality and Testing, Robotics
   (AQTR), Cluj-Napoca, ROMANIA, MAY 16-18, 2024},
Organization = {IEEE},
Abstract = {Legal investigation of digital data storage systems involves the
   application of specific methods and procedures that assures quick
   retrieval of relevant information as well as veracity and security of
   collected data. This paper aims to explore the potential and benefits of
   using artificial intelligence ( AI) technology in the field of computer
   investigation. Using a series of specific techniques, computer system
   investigators can enhance their efficiency in analyzing and identifying
   evidence. Automatic classification of data present on a storage device
   can increase the accuracy and reduce the effort of a human investigator.
   Forensic analysis of a storage device requires integration of a sequence
   of steps beginning with the (re)construction of the storage device's
   image till the semantic interpretation of the content. The paper
   proposes a processing sequence that includes some AI methods for
   relevant data search and classification.},
