Organization = {Canakkale Onsekiz Mart Univ},
Abstract = {This work aims to use Python and OpenCV libraries to create a smart
   camera system that can function independently and help people. The
   suggested system can also identify absent items using the frame
   difference technique. It also has a recording function, an alert
   function for people entering the room, and an alert function for
   detecting motion. This project's functions include normal recording,
   monitoring, recognizing members, detecting noise, and detecting visits
   in rooms. To identify motion, the SSIM approach is employed by the
   monitor feature; the LBPH algorithm is utilized for face recognition;
   and the video writer function of OpenCV is used to record live video
   while the visitor detection feature keeps an eye out for new faces.
   Numerous iterations of the intended project's execution have been tried,
   yielding its own results. The outcomes were commensurate with
   expectations. Functionality testing showed that the features were useful
   in achieving their goals. The Python graphical user interface (GUI)
   program is utilized, and it may run on any PC with a webcam or USB
   camera. The system incorporates a number of characteristics that may
   detect and identify criminal activity, making it simpler for law
   enforcement to apprehend and prosecute offenders while satisfying the
   security demands of individuals and businesses. Only a few potential
   additions to the proposed project are mentioned.},
