Number = {3},
Pages = {1167-1188},
Month = {SEP-DEC},
Abstract = {Modern society is dominated by new technologies, which have a quick
   expansion and a dramatic expansive attitude, in every area of individual
   and collective life. In the field of criminal proceedings, too, the use
   of advanced technological tools changes significantly the features of
   the system, with a visible impact on practices, but also on rights,
   safeguards and basic rules. This essay proposes a view of the areas of
   criminal justice where this phenomenon is more evident and of the main
   implications it has, in the perspective of protection of the basic
   principles of criminal proceedings and of fundamental rights of
   individuals.},
